                    "company": "Erasmus MC",
                    "description": "Worked in the Biomedical Imaging Group of Rotterdam on the project \"Developing Tool for Hyperthermia treatment planning\". This project was carried in collaboration with the Hyperthermia Unit of the Erasmus MC Radiotherapy department and was funded by STW technology foundation. \nThe aim of the project was to improve the automated generation of 3D patient model for Hyperthermia treatment planning (HTP). From the image processing point of view two parts can be distinguished:\n- Development an automatic segmentation algorithm for the tissues in the head and neck anatomy which are relevant for HTP. The idea is to integrate magnetic resonance (MR) images with computed tomography (CT) images to improve the segmentation accuracy and precision to automatically segment these tissues. \n- Development and integration of patient specific thermal model for HTP. MR angiography can be used to generate models for the patient vasculature. Blood perfusion lead to heat dispersion in the patient during the hypethermia treatment. Modeling this effect may have a large improvement on the treatment planning quality.",
